<subSubSection id="C30C65361B2DFFCF9A9498A835C0FA3A" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA936BD1B2DFFCF9A9498A835C0FA3A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1178,2031]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2DFFCF9A9498A8372EFB12" bold="true" box="[199,321,1250,1275]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head light castaneous dorsally; outline of each mandibular plate black. Each anterior angle of pronotum with a stout, spine-like tubercle, barely surpassing lateral margin of each compound eye; each anterolateral margin with stout tubercles; each humeral angle bilobed apically, with two processes anteriorly and one process posteriorly; each posterolateral margin sinuated, with a median tubercle; posterior margin weakly concave (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF9B5B9938373BFA62" box="[264,340,1394,1419]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1812,1835]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,949,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,945,1789]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Schematic drawings of pronotum of Braunus Distant, 1899 in dorsal view. 1 – 3. B. sciocorinus (Walker, 1867); 4. B. machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov.; 5. B. gibbus Garbelotto &amp; Barão sp. nov.; 6. B. prionotus Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov.; 7. B. asperus (McDonald, 1982) comb. nov.; 8. B. ateuchus (Brailovski &amp; Rolston, 1986) comb. nov.; 9. B. bordoni (Thomas, 1997) comb. nov.; 10. B. brettlizorum (Thomas, 1997) comb. nov.; 11. B. ocellatus (Thomas, 2001) comb. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261495/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9B109939373BFA62" box="[323,340,1395,1419]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apex of hemelytral radial vein calloused; corium reaching abdominal segment VII. Male genitalia: posterolateral angles of pygophore quadrate; inferior layer of ventral rim strongly emarginated, with bilobed projection medially; parameres rounded apically (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF994C99F035CCFA3A" box="[799,931,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF990B99F135CCFA3A" box="[856,931,1467,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="40.5" valueMax="43.0" valueMin="38.0">38–43</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C65361B2DFFCE9A949994355AFE8C" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA936BD1B2DFFCF9A9499943277F84E" blockId="6.[151,1437,1178,2031]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2DFFCF9A9499943736FA1E" bold="true" box="[199,345,1502,1527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">Description.</emphasis>
Body color mottled dark brown and yellowish, predominantly yellowish dorsally and dark brown ventrally; head yellowish, outline of each mandibular plate black dorsally; labial apex brown; anterior and posterior margins of each connexival segment black, yellow medially; legs yellowish with brown spots (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF9F549A6C33FFF9D6" box="[1287,1424,1574,1599]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9F169A6C33FFF9D6" box="[1349,1424,1574,1599]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="36.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="36.0">36–37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mandibular plates longer than clypeus. Proportion of antennal segments: I=II&lt;III=IV&lt;V. Labial apex attaining posterior margin of metasternum. Spiny projection at each anterior angle of pronotum directed anterolaterad, barely exceeding lateral limit of each compound eye. Anterolateral margins of pronotum each bearing 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9E929AD932A0F942" box="[1217,1231,1683,1707]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9E8C9AD93282F942" box="[1247,1261,1683,1707]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="2.0">2</number>
well-produced, finger-like tubercles; each humeral angle bilobed apically, with two processes anteriorly and one process posteriorly; posterolateral margins sinuate, each with a median tubercle; pronotal disc calloused between cicatrices; cicatrices swollen (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF9B249AB437ADF8FE" box="[375,450,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1812,1835]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,949,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,945,1789]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Schematic drawings of pronotum of Braunus Distant, 1899 in dorsal view. 1 – 3. B. sciocorinus (Walker, 1867); 4. B. machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov.; 5. B. gibbus Garbelotto &amp; Barão sp. nov.; 6. B. prionotus Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov.; 7. B. asperus (McDonald, 1982) comb. nov.; 8. B. ateuchus (Brailovski &amp; Rolston, 1986) comb. nov.; 9. B. bordoni (Thomas, 1997) comb. nov.; 10. B. brettlizorum (Thomas, 1997) comb. nov.; 11. B. ocellatus (Thomas, 2001) comb. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261495/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9BE29AB537ADF8FE" box="[433,450,1791,1815]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum reaching posterior margin of abdominal segment VI; lateral margins of scutellum each with shallow excavation; scutellum swollen longitudinally, medially; postfrenal lobe about 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9F0B9B69330DF8D2" box="[1368,1378,1827,1851]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9F3D9B693313F8D2" box="[1390,1404,1827,1851]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="3.0">3</number>
of length of frenal lobe. Corium longer than scutellum, reaching anterior margin of abdominal segment VII; hemelytral membrane surpassing apex of abdomen; veins coarse, reticulate. Hind wings reduced. Mesosternum with median carina slightly elevated. Metasternum with shallow median furrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936BD1B2DFFCE9A949BF8348CFF11" blockId="6.[151,1437,1178,2031]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,501]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="175" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2DFFCF9A949BF83714F822" bold="true" box="[199,379,1970,1995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Dorsal rim concave with 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF98F99BF934D9F822" box="[682,694,1971,1995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF98999BF934B9F822" box="[714,726,1971,1995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="1.0">1</number>
flap-like projections laterally to segment X (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF9EB39BF8330BF822" box="[1248,1380,1970,1995]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF9F489BF9330BF822" box="[1307,1380,1971,1995]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="38.5" valueMax="39.0" valueMin="38.0">38–39</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2DFFCF9F209BF833E3F822" box="[1395,1420,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">dr</emphasis>
). Each posterolateral angle quadrate bearing tufts of setae (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2DFFCF997B9B9C35C3F806" box="[808,940,2006,2031]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2DFFCF99319B9D35C3F806" box="[866,940,2007,2031]" pageId="6" pageNumber="174" value="38.5" valueMax="39.0" valueMin="38.0">38–39</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2DFFCF99EA9B9235BAF806" box="[953,981,2008,2031]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="174">pa</emphasis>
). Inferior layer of ventral rim projected posteriorly, bilobed apically (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2CFFCE9BB49CDD3404FF59" box="[487,619,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2CFFCE98719CD23404FF59" box="[546,619,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175" value="42.5" valueMax="43.0" valueMin="42.0">42–43</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2CFFCE982A9CD334FFFF59" box="[633,656,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">vr</emphasis>
); superior layer of ventral rim depressed medially (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2CFFCE9EB59CDD3305FF59" box="[1254,1386,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2CFFCE9F729CD23305FF59" box="[1313,1386,152,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175" value="39.5" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="38.0">38–41</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2CFFCE9F2A9CDD33E3FF59" box="[1401,1420,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">sl</emphasis>
). Segment X rectangular (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2CFFCE9BF59CF63448FF3D" box="[422,551,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
Figs 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2CFFCE9B8D9CF63448FF3D" box="[478,551,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175" value="39.5" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="38.0">38–41</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2CFFCE98619CF7342CFF3D" box="[562,579,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
<collectionCode id="ED07AE781B2CFFCE98619CF7342CFF3D" box="[562,579,189,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">X</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
). Parameres F-shaped; paramere head blade-like, rounded apically; in lateral view, with a rounded, median process (
<figureCitation id="132D2A381B2CFFCE981F9C9534F0FF11" box="[588,671,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,555,1615]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,555,1616]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Braunus machadoi Barão &amp; Garbelotto sp. nov. 36 – 37. habitus; 36. dorsal view; 37. ventral view; 38 – 43. pygophore; 38 – 39. dorsal view; 40 – 41. posterior view; 42 – 43. ventral view. Abbreviations: dr = dorsal rim; pa = posterolateral angle; par = paramere; sl = mid depression of superior layer of ventral rim; vr = ventral rim; X = abdominal segment X. Scale bars: 35 – 36 = 2 mm; 37 – 42 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261499/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDE249A1B2CFFCE98D39CAA34F0FF11" box="[640,671,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175" value="41.0">41</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<emphasis id="B962EAAF1B2CFFCE98F89CAB34BDFF11" box="[683,722,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">par</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936BD1B2CFFCE9A949D4E355AFE8C" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="175">
